ed a corporate responsibility report as we continue to grow as a global security company we remain dedicated to delivering the highest levels of corporate responsibility grounded by our commitment to our company values said wes bush northrop grummans chairman chief executive officer and president the  crr is consistent with the global reporting initiative gri g sustainability reporting guidelines gri is a thirdparty organization that has developed a widelyused environmental social and governance reporting framework the report is also evaluated by an independent external review panel that provides feedback and advice from a stakeholder perspective the crr is available online at httpwwwnorthropgrummancomcorporateresponsibilitypagesreportsaspx corporate responsibility is a key component in helping northrop grumman sustain its top performance in our industry said sandra eversmanly northrop grummans vice president of global corporate responsibility and president of the northrop grumman foundation this report illustrates that corporate responsibility is ingrained in our values and is essential to the commitments we make to our stakeholders and to building the best culture at northrop grumman some  report highlights include the dow jones sustainability north america index recognized northrop grumman as one of the top aerospace and defense companies for corporate sustainability performance we maintained our focus on building the best culture at northrop grumman with diversity and inclusion central to that goal recognition we received included being named a top company for executive women earning a perfect rating on the disability equality index listing best places to work for individuals with disabilities and being ranked st on diversityincs annual list for the top  companies for diversity  we reflected our commitment to ethical business conduct in our supply chain through a new supplier standards of business conduct  in support of global communities where we live and work 