 lunar module grumman llv number of employees   subsidiaries grumman aerospace corp grumman allied industries inc grumman data systems corp the grumman aircraft engineering corporation later grumman aerospace corporation was a leading th century us producer of military and civilian aircraft founded on december   by leroy grumman and partners its independent existence ended in  when it was acquired by northrop corporation to form northrop grumman contents  history  long island location  products  aircraft  spacecraft  other products  references  notes  bibliography  external links historyedit grumman historical marker leroy grumman and others worked for the loening aircraft engineering corporation in the s but when it was bought by keystone aircraft corporation and the operations moved from new york city to bristol pennsylvania grumman and his partners edmund ward poor william schwendler jake swirbul and clint towl started their own company in an old coxklemin aircraft co factory in baldwin on long island new york all of the early grumman employees were former loening employees the company was named after grumman because he was its largest investor the company filed as a business on december   and opened its doors on january   keeping busy by welding aluminum tubing for truck frames the company eagerly pursued contracts with the us navy grumman designed the first practical floats with a retractable landing gear for the navy and this launched grumman into the aviation market the first grumman aircraft was also for the navy the grumman ff a biplane with retractable landing gear this was followed by a number of other successful designs grumman corporation logo ca  during world war ii grumman became known for its cats navy fighter aircraft ff wildcat and ff hellcat and the less well known grumman ff tigercat and grumman ff bearcat neither of which saw combat during world war ii and for its torpedo bomber tbf avenger grumman ranked nd among united states corporations in the value of wartime production contracts grummans first jet aircraft was the ff panther it was followed by the upgraded fff cougar and the less well known f tiger in the s the companys big postwar successes came in the s with the a intruder and e hawkeye and in the s with the grumman eab prowler and f tomcat grumman products were prominent in the film top gun and numerous world war ii naval and marine corps aviation films the us navy still employs the hawkeye as part of carrier air wings on board aircraft carriers and the us marine corps still operates the prowler as of  apollo spacecraft apollo lunar module diagram grumman was the chief contractor on the apollo lunar module that landed men on the moon the firm received the contract on november   and built  lunar modules as the apollo program neared its end grumman was one of the main competitors for the contract to design and build the space shuttle but lost to rockwell international the company ended up involved in the shuttle program nonetheless as a subcontractor to rockwell providing the wings and vertical stabilizer sections in  the company changed its name to grumman aerospace corporation and in  it sold the grummanamerican division to gulfstream aerospace the company built the grumman long life vehicle llv a light transport mail truck designed for and used by the united states postal service the llv entered service in  grumman was responsible for a successful line of business aircraft including the gulfstream i turboprop grumman model g and gulfstream ii business jet grumman model g which were operated by a number of companies and private individuals as well as by government agencies including various military entities and nasa in addition the gulfstream i propjet was operated by several commuterregional airlines in scheduled passenger services and included a stretched version being the gulfstream ic grumman model gc which could transport  passengers gulfstream business jets continue to be currently manufactured by gulfstream aerospace which is a wholly owned subsidiary of general dynamics long island locationedit f tomcat at grumman memorial park calverton new york grumman intruder grumman tracer grummans former headquarters in bethpage now altice usa formerly cablevision headquarters for much of the cold war period grumman was the largest corporate employer on long islandcitation needed grummans products were considered so reliable and ruggedly built that the company was often referred to as the grumman iron works as the company grew it moved to valley stream new york then farmingdale new york finally to bethpage new york with the testing and final assembly at the acre  km naval weapons station in calverton new york all located on long island at its peak in  it employed  people on long island and occupied  square feet  m in structures on  acres  km it leased from the us navy in bethpage the end of the cold war at the beginning of the s reduced defense spending and led to a wave of mergers as aerospace companies shrank in number in  northrop bought grumman for  billion to form northrop grumman after northrop topped a  billion offer from martin marietta the new company closed almost all of its facilities on long island and converted the bethpage plant to a residential and office complex with its headquarters becoming the corporate headquarters for cablevision and the calverton plant being turned into an airport developed by riverhead new yorkcitation needed former aircraft hangars have become grumman studios a film and television production center a portion of the airport property has been used for the grumman memorial park northrop grummans remaining business at the bethpage campus is the battle management and engagement systems division which employs around  peoplewhencitation needed productsedit an fa tomcat of vf jolly rogers in the old color scheme from the beginning of its service an ae intruder flying over spain during exercise matador tbf avenger navy grumman usc tracker ec hawkeye aircraftedit the cats grumman ff wildcat grumman ff hellcat grumman ff tigercat grumman ff bearcat grumman ff panther grumman ff f cougar grumman xff jaguar grumman f tiger grumman fff super tiger grumman f tomcat other fighter aircraft grumman ff grumman ff grumman ff grumman xff skyrocket grumman xp general dynamicsgrumman fb grumman g amphibious columbia xjl grumman jf duck grumman jf duck grumman g goose some modified as super or turbo goose grumman g widgeon grumman g mallard grumman hu albatross coast guard ufuf navy u civilian g grumman g tadpole attack grumman a intruder bomber grumman xsbf grumman tbf avenger grumman xtbf grumman xtsf electronic warfare aircraft grumman eab prowler general dynamics–grumman efa raven other aircraft grumman af guardian grumman c trader grumman e tracer grumman s tracker grumman e hawkeye grumman c greyhound grumman ov mohawk grumman x civilian grumman gulfstream i grumman gulfstream ii grumman american aa – grumman american aab trainer – grumman american aa traveler – grumman american aaa cheetah – grumman american aab tiger – grumman american cougar grumman ag cat grumman kitten spacecraftedit space apollo lunar module other productsedit grumman olson built aluminum truck bodies known as stepvans under the grumman olson brand it made the p and p step vans for ups grumman manufactured fire engines under the name firecat and aerial tower trucks under the aerialcat name the company entered the fire apparatus business in  with its purchase of howe fire apparatus and ended operations in  grumman canoes were developed in  as world war ii was winding down company executive william hoffman used the companys aircraft aluminum to replace the traditional wood design the canoes had a reputation for being sturdier lighter and stronger than their wood counterparts and had a considerable market share grumman moved its boat making division to marathon new york in  outboard marine corp bought the division in  and produced the last grummanbrand canoe in  shortly thereafter former grumman executives formed the marathon boat group to produce the canoes in  the group worked out an agreement with northrop grumman to sell the canoes using grumman name and logo the grumman canoes with its logo are used in the film deliverance after grumman took over howe fire apparatus the fire trucks were rebranded grumman grumman sport boat grummanflxible  transit buses – ben franklin px a science submarine grumman llv postal vehicle widely used by the united states postal service and canada post in  grumman leased the first superconducting mri in manhattan to east river medical imaging then known as sk magnetic resonance imaging pc united states postal service grumman llv  grumman firecat santiago de chile fd  grumman olson ups truck grumman kabmaster hostess delivery truck referencesedit notesedit  air warfare an international encyclopedia volume two mz volume  pp –  a b c d e f jordan corey c grummans ascendency chapter one planes and pilots of world war   retrieved july    peck merton j  scherer frederic m the weapons acquisition process an economic analysis  harvard business school p  skrula and gregory   long islanders shocked by grummans merger the new york times march    a b commercial propertyselling off northrop grummans surplus cablevision takes last of the grumman buildings the new york times december    northrop bests martin marietta to buy grumman the new york times april    a b c jordan corey c grummans ascendency chapter two planes and pilots of world war   retrieved july    jordan corey c grummans ascendency chapter three planes and pilots of world war   retrieved july    paddling a canoe to success newsday retrieved may    marathon boatgroup about us marathonboatcom retrieved may   bibliographyedit ferguson robert g one thousand planes a day ford grumman general motors and the arsenal of democracy history and technology volume  issue   fetherston drew pioneers on the runway raising gr