viewnorthrop grumman corporation was founded in  and is headquartered in falls church virginia in the washington dc area this public company has nearly  employees worldwide and an annual revenue of over  billionone of the top global security companies northrop grumman makes some of the most advanced technology in the aerospace and defense industry the company develops unmanned systems and cybersecurity products and solutions for both government and corporate customers around the worldnorthrop grumman corporation job opportunitiesnorthrop grumman has built a workforce composed of some of the worlds top electronics technology and information systems professionals the company regularly seeks additional top candidates in these fieldsengineering professionals take on conceptual design and related analysis of highly specialized aerospace and defense equipment they also test prototypes review designs and produce successful components candidates must typically hold a masters degree in engineering along with knowledge of a coding language and the ability to work in a collaborative environmentpricing and contracts professionals administer and negotiate contracts and pricing agreements they ensure that contracts meet both corporate policies and legal requirements candidates typically need a bachelors degree in business administration and a predetermined level of security clearanceassembly professionals create aerospace and defense parts and products they manually move and adjust parts and perform tasks like sawing riveting and drilling they continually monitor quality and control various elements of the assembly process candidates typically need a high school diploma and experience working in the fieldnorthrop grumman corporation work culturenorthrop grumman maintains a commitment to fostering both product development and employee development the company encourages its staff members to provide community service in their local areas and supports science and engineering educatio